<span id="freeTextContainer8615638901074999304">Although at times Raspail seems to be getting carried away in his description of the depravity of the third-world invaders, his description of the reaction of the European elite to the crisis is spot on. I am still amazed that such a book was written decades ago when it is so relevant to what is happening in the world now. What is even more amazing is that Raspail is a Frenchman. Maybe there is yet a glimmer of hope for the le peuple gallois.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


